genresAdvancedInfo.name: japanese orchestra
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Japanese orchestra is a classical music genre that features traditional Japanese instruments such as the koto, shakuhachi, and shamisen. The music is characterized by its use of pentatonic scales and unique harmonies. It often reflects the natural beauty and cultural traditions of Japan.
